    public interface FiniteRepresentation
    This interface marks automata types that have a finite representation, i.e. can be represented by a finite number of entities. Note that this does not necessarily correspond to states in the usual sense (like in the case of SimpleAutomaton). For example, push-down systems can have infinitely many states but may be representable with a finite amount of locations.
